description:
Welcome to Scoro! 🙌 
This “Getting Started” project will guide you through the whole implementation process: 

How to approach the onboarding process
Understand different ways of working with Scoro & design your workflows
Configure your site based on the workflows you have chosen
Onboard your team and support them through the change

Your Service Delivery Manager will assign you tasks to complete in your Getting Started project as you move through the onboarding process. Update the statuses of your tasks to reflect your progress, and when complete, mark the tasks as 'done'. 
Please remember to set aside at least 2-4 hours in between each meeting with your Service Delivery Manager to work on your tasks and test your Scoro workflows.
Our Support team are also here to assist you with any day-today issues or platform how to's. They are available Mon-Fri. You can reach them on support@scoro.com or submit a help ticket here.

It covers three years, starting in March 2025 with some specific deliverables each year: - Issue 5 press releases announcing the campaign sent to a relevant food and consumer mailing list of media publications gaining a minimum of - - 15 guaranteed pieces of campaign coverage - Online advertising: one banner ad over 28 days achieving 1.2m impressions - 20 meetings with food influencer personnel in a culinary institute environment, educating relevant people on Olive oil benefits - 70 promotional days in restaurants, sampling oil, giving away leaflets, with pictures taken at each event. - 60 retail supermarket environments, 2 days per location, executing handing out a leaflet, banner and sampling olive oil, with a picture taken - The creative artwork, copy and materials will be developed centrally in the US and issued to the partner in Japan, some assistance with language, checking the cultural fit will be required.
Jermaine Parkin to be deal owner.
